President Biden held a virtual meeting with industry and labor leaders to discuss the importance of passing the CHIPS for America Act. The act aims to strengthen the national and economic security of the United States by increasing domestic semiconductor production. The meeting focused on the national security implications of relying on foreign semiconductor production, as well as the economic opportunities that increased domestic production can bring. The participants highlighted the importance of semiconductors in various industries, including defense, healthcare, and transportation. They emphasized that passing the CHIPS Act is critical to ensure a secure supply chain, create jobs, and maintain the country's technological leadership. President Biden expressed his support for the bill and urged Congress to pass it as soon as possible.